metadata.name: Ring Folk #94
metadata.description:
For the Ring Folk, shape and colour don't matter, however, some mutated features give them special abilities.

Background Radiation
Ring Folk emanate natural ring radiation, but only the glitch pattern allows them to alter reality, or should I say corrupt? +1 Rank point

Eyes
Awakened Ring Folk have an extra eye, but they can't see with it. Gives it's bearer the ability to see past, present and future. +1 Rank point

Head
Prominent horns, tiny ears, others have nothing at all. There's a peculiar mutation where Attuned individuals are able to share thoughts and emotions with each other wherever they might be in the metaverse. +1 Rank point

Rings
They like to show off their arm rings and the more the nobler. Up to +2 Rank points

Ring Symmetry
Even numbers and symmetry seem to be very coveted among them. They might only have 2 rings, but can still look sophisticated. +1 Rank point

Rank
Most Ring Folk are ranked C and B, but some are mutated or wealthy enough to be A rank or even S rank if they're lucky.

metadata.name: Fractures #67
metadata.description:
Fractures is a personal interpretation of how beauty can emerge from broken shapes.

Starting from a simple and regular geometric shape, Fractures succeeds in breaking the initial visual monotony thanks to a recursive division system applied to the triangles of the initial polygon. Line patterns, random color inversions, grainy and charcoal effect are then added to give the final image a nice organic feel.

Press [P] to generate and save a 4000x4000 .png file. This can take some time, be patient.

Artist: Estienne
Dec 2021

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #18
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Anachronous #35
metadata.description:
This project is about the exploration of chaotic structures created with lines and blurry silhouettes. They work together to make the shapes emerge without revealing them completely and create dark and light areas that compose a feeling of depth and weight to the scene.

Some pieces are chaotic, some more ordered. Some have strong compositions, some don't. By zooming in on the details we can let our mind wander and start seeing shapes.

Best experienced in full-screen.

Press S to take a screenshot
Press M to take a high resolution screenshot
Press H to take a higher resolution screenshot (may not work for some devices)

WARNING: Project is using webgl, it may not work on some older devices.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Almost Vertical Lines #50
metadata.description:
Hundreds of lines move and change their inclination without ever overlapping and only occasionally remaining vertical. The additional perceived movements are generated by the difficulty of completely eliminating the aliasing of almost vertical lines. Small rescaling of the frames makes the configurations and their transformations even more elaborate. 

The movements of all lines and the rescaling of the frames are determined by eight parameters with decimal values. The cycles that are generated can therefore have quite long durations.

Antonio Belluscio (@livinbits)
October 2017 - April 2022

Viewing in fullscreen mode and landscape orientation is recommended.
The algorithm was implemented in p5.js without using shaders.

metadata.name: Resilience  #44
metadata.description:
Resilience is a collection of endless architectures.
In a resilient generative system composed of multiple compatible parts, real-time information exchange enables open reconfigurations and continuous discrete adjustments. Sometimes vague and fuzzy, sometimes real and tangible, they reveal different readings of architectural complexity and scale: from city plans to floor plans and details to sections and elevations.

Resilience comes in a variety of polychrome palettes, ascii glyphs, and styles. 
To enjoy it in full-screen mode, press the left mouse button in live mode, for a monochrome look press 'b'. Made with P5js.

Resilience Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022
